            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"sae-width-scaling-how-many-features-do-you-need\">SAE Width Scaling: How Many Features Do You Need?</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">We pass Gemma 3 12B activations through Gemma Scope 2 SAEs at four dictionary widths\n(16k, 65k, 262k, 1M) and ask: how does refusal feature discovery scale with width?</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Key finding:</strong> The biggest jump is 16k to 65k. After 262k, returns plateau \u2014\nbut the dictionary <em>reorganizes</em> rather than just growing (only 28-41% of 16k features survive to 1M).</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
